## Acceptance
- [ ] When the server is spawned as a child process, it listens on the port from process.env.PORT (and on 3000 when PORT is unset) and serves requests there — asserted by the test spawning the process and issuing a real HTTP request.
- [ ] The on-disk store is created on first boot and its schema initialization is idempotent (spawning the server a second time against an existing store does not error).
- [ ] The repository layer round-trips user, project, and task records: a record written through the store before the server process stops is still readable after the process is restarted against the same on-disk file.
- [ ] A request with malformed JSON, an unknown route, or an oversized body receives a structured JSON error response with an appropriate 4xx status and the spawned server process stays up (a subsequent request still succeeds).
- [ ] A route module placed in src/routes/ is auto-mounted by the router without edits to src/server.js or src/router.js, and the router exposes an injection point for an auth verifier applied to routes marked protected — demonstrated by the unauthenticated GET /health route returning 200.
- [ ] `package.json` has a "start" script that launches the server, and the on-disk data file/directory is git-ignored.

## Verify
- node --test tests/foundation.test.js (contract)
- npm run typecheck (validate)

